frsqrte(sign, exp, mant)
{
    // The first 16 bases and deltas are all even; they're probably stored
    // internally in 1 bit less and shifted left.
    base[] = {0x7FF4,0x7852,0x7154,0x6AE4,0x64F2,0x5F6E,0x5A4C,0x5580,
              0x5102,0x4CCA,0x48D0,0x450E,0x4182,0x3E24,0x3AF2,0x37E8,
              0x34FD,0x2F97,0x2AA5,0x2618,0x21E4,0x1DFE,0x1A5C,0x16F8,
              0x13CA,0x10CE,0x0DFE,0x0B57,0x08D4,0x0673,0x0431,0x020B}
    delta[] = {0x7A4,0x700,0x670,0x5F2,0x584,0x524,0x4CC,0x47E,
               0x43A,0x3FA,0x3C2,0x38E,0x35E,0x332,0x30A,0x2E6,
               0x568,0x4F3,0x48D,0x435,0x3E7,0x3A2,0x365,0x32E,
               0x2FC,0x2D0,0x2A8,0x283,0x261,0x243,0x226,0x20B}
    if exp == 0 and mant == 0 return sign, 255, 0  // infinity
    if exp == 255 and mant != 0 return sign, 255, mant | 1<<22  // quieted NaN
    if sign return QNaN  // VXSQRT
    if exp == 255 and mant == 0 return 0, 0, 0  // zero
    exp, mant = normalize(exp, mant)
    index = mant>>48 | (exp & 1 ? 0 : 16)
    exp = (3068 - exp) >> 1
    mant = ( (base[index]<<11) - (delta[index] * (mant>>37 & 0x7FF)) ) << 26
    return 0, exp, mant
}
